INSIGHTS - AdOptics Managed Services Landing Page

APPLICATION STRUCTURE:
- Static HTML landing page for AdOptics Managed Services
- Uses Tailwind CSS for styling with custom theme configuration
- Responsive design with mobile-first approach
- JavaScript for interactive components (mobile menu, accordions)

KEY FEATURES:
- Fully responsive navigation with mobile hamburger menu
- Hero section promoting Google Ads management services
- Service sections targeting SaaS, Ecommerce, and Lead-Gen brands ($5K+/mo spend)
- Testimonials/reviews section
- 4-step service workflow explanation
- Flat-rate pricing at $990/month
- FAQ accordion functionality
- Complete footer with social links

TECHNICAL DETAILS:
- Uses Inter font from Google Fonts
- Custom Tailwind theme with AdOptics brand colors
- Mobile breakpoint set at 992px
- Accessible components with ARIA attributes
- Event delegation for better performance
- CSS Grid and Flexbox for layouts

MOBILE/IOS SAFARI NOTE:
- To prevent horizontal overflow on cards with media, wrap sections with `overflow-hidden` and ensure images are `w-full h-auto` on mobile with a reasonable `max-w`.

BRAND POSITIONING:
- Targets businesses spending $5K+/month on ads
- Focuses on SKAG campaigns and dynamic landing pages
- Promises hands-free management and ROAS improvement
- Flat-rate pricing model (no ad spend markup)
- Emphasis on results within 2-4 weeks

DEPLOYMENT TARGET:
- Intended to be deployed at https://managed.adoptics.com
- Connected to GitHub repo: https://github.com/sprfrkr/adoptics_managed.git
